column1: tammo-meijer-18246311,Tammo,Meijer,Coordinator Education/Innovation International Business Programme ,https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4E03AQGQAUtcKcZdXQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1611765217725?e=1697673600&v=beta&t=VCQnKXTIPLU27jhHFAJNKaOF_upaZ-0CQjZyuvB5dog,,personal,ACoAAAJhezIBCii85q4qrCXQA0Aowjoe0sbrDm0,39942962,,"I’ve been working for  more than 20 years in Higher Education at the University of Applied Sciences in Zwolle, The Netherlands.
I started my working life as a teacher of German Language at a College for  Vocational Education with focus on middle-management training.
After two years  I switched  into a new field of teaching : Financial Services Management

In 1993 I was appointed as a lecturer of German Language and German Business culture at the HEAO, a School for Higher Economic Education, a part of the Hogeschool Windesheim, nowadays Windesheim University of Applied Sciences.
The HEAO has been  tranformed into the Business School of Windesheim University and is now part of the Division Business, Media and Law.
Previously I was engaged in the following activities:

column2: Teaching German, Financial Management Services and Sales
International Contacts (with Partner Universities in Europe)
For RABO Bank Academie in Utrecht : lecturing and organising Business trips to Germany, UK and Austria)
Teacher Education ( German at the School of Education)
